      en: 'Khachapuri is arguably Georgia\'s most iconic dish — a cheese-filled bread that has as many variations as there are regions. The most famous version, Adjarian khachapuri from Batumi, is shaped like a boat with a raw egg and butter melting into the molten cheese. It\'s said to represent a fisherman\'s boat on the Black Sea, with the egg symbolizing the sun.\n\nKhachapuri is so culturally significant that economists created the "Khachapuri Index" — similar to The Economist\'s Big Mac Index — to track inflation in Georgia by monitoring the cost of its ingredients. Each region takes immense pride in its own version: Imeretian (round), Megrelian (double-cheese topped), Adjarian (boat-shaped), and Achma (layered like lasagna).',
      es: 'El khachapuri es posiblemente el plato más icónico de Georgia — un pan relleno de queso que tiene tantas variaciones como regiones hay. La versión más famosa, el khachapuri adjaro de Batumi, tiene forma de barca con un huevo crudo y mantequilla derritiéndose en el queso fundido. Se dice que representa la barca de un pescador en el Mar Negro, con el huevo simbolizando el sol.\n\nEl khachapuri es tan culturalmente significativo que los economistas crearon el "Índice Khachapuri" — similar al Índice Big Mac de The Economist — para rastrear la inflación en Georgia monitoreando el costo de sus ingredientes.',
